# Hebrew & RTL

## App shell

- **English, LTR** for all chrome: nav, labels, dates, settings, slot names (Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, Snacks).
- Do **not** set `dir="rtl"` on `<html>` or layout root.

## Meal text only

```tsx
<span dir="auto" lang="he" className="text-end">
  {meal.text}
</span>
```

- Input: `dir="auto"`, `lang="he"`, appropriate `inputMode` / font for Hebrew.
- Test mixed Hebrew/English and numerals on **iOS Safari** early.

## Icons (from PRD)

- ⓘ → reasoning, assumptions, editable breakdown
- 🔗 when `searched: true` → sources
- ⚠️ when `confidence: "low"` → clarification text

## shadcn + Tailwind

- Use existing design tokens; mobile-first spacing; bottom sheets for add/edit flows.
- Calorie numbers stay **prominent** (LTR numerals even beside RTL text).
